<h3 id="try-hourly-check-ins">Try <em>hourly</em> check-ins</h3>

<p>Apply mindfulness to productivity by regularly <em>checking</em> in with yourself to notice if youâ€™re <em>moving</em> through your day with focus.</p>

<p><a href="https://bregmanpartners.com/">Peter Bergman</a>, an executive coach and the best-<em>selling</em> author of 18 Minutes, <a href="https://hbr.org/2009/07/an-18minute-plan-for-managing">suggests</a> setting a regular <em>timer</em> to refocus ourselves:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>â€œSet your watch, phone, or <em>computer</em> to ring every hour. When it rings, take a deep breath, look at your list and ask yourself if you <em>spent</em> your last hour productively. Then look at your <em>calendar</em> and <em>deliberately</em> <em>recommit</em> to how you are <em>going</em> to use the next hour. Manage your day hour by hour. Donâ€™t let the hours manage you.â€</p>
