  <p>â€œAt the end of the day I want to have <em>zero</em> tasks on my today list. The truth is that most days I donâ€™t complete everything on my today list and I <em>postpone</em> things. This isnâ€™t a negative thing. I see it as an opportunity to take stock of where Iâ€™m at, re-evaluate my tasks, and re-plan them.â€</p>
